6 of a prior violation of driving under the influence, including a violation of 61-8-1002(1)(a), (1)(b), (1)(c), or (1)(d),
7 an offense that meets the definition of aggravated driving under the influence, or a similar offense under
8 previous laws of this state or the laws of another state; or
9 (d) the person refuses to give a breath sample as required in 61-8-1016 and the person's driver's
10 license or privilege to drive was suspended, cancelled, or revoked under the provisions of an implied consent
11 statute.
12 (2)(3) "Alcoholic beverage" means a compound produced for human consumption as a drink that
13 contains 0.5% or more of alcohol by volume.
14 (3)(4) "Alcohol concentration" means either grams of alcohol per 100 milliliters of blood or grams of
15 alcohol per 210 liters of breath, including as used in 16-6-305, 23-2-535, 45-5-207, 67-1-211, and this title.
16 (4)(5) "Bus" means a motor vehicle with a manufacturer's rated seating capacity of 11 or more
17 passengers, including the driver.
18 (5)(6) "Camper" has the meaning provided in 61-1-101.
19 (6)(7) "Commercial motor vehicle" has the meaning provided in 61-1-101.
20 (7)(8) "Drug" means any substance that when taken into the human body can impair a person's ability
21 to operate a vehicle safely. The term includes the meanings provided in 50-32-101(6), (7), and (14).
22 (8)(9) "DUI court" means any court that has established a special docket for handling cases involving
23 persons convicted under 61-8-1007 or 61-8-1008 and that implements a program of incentives and sanctions
24 intended to assist a participant to complete treatment ordered pursuant to 61-8-1009 and to end the
25 participant's criminal behavior associated with the use of alcohol or drugs.
26 (9)(10) "Highway" has the meaning provided in 61-1-101, including the shoulders of the highway.
27 (10)(11)"Motor home" has the meaning provided in 61-1-101.
28 (11)(12)"Motor vehicle" has the meaning provided in 61-1-101.
